            <div class="md:bg-white md:rounded-xl md:shadow-sm md:border md:border-slate-200 overflow-hidden">
              <div class="bg-emerald-600 text-white px-4 py-2.5">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide">FAQ highlights</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="p-4 space-y-3 text-xs text-slate-600">
                <p>
                  <strong class="text-slate-800">Do I need MRI for every AC sprain?</strong><br />
                  No — standard radiographs aligned with consensus guidance usually suffice for the AC joint itself<RefLink
                    id="10"
                    text="ESSKA paper"
                    url={references[9].url}
                  />.
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong class="text-slate-800">Hook plate vs buttons?</strong><br />
                  Buttons / tape avoid the subacromial hook and often eliminate planned removal surgery; hook plates remain in
                  use but carry higher reoperation burden<RefLink id="1" text="RCT" url={references[0].url} /><RefLink
                    id="6"
                    text="Network MA"
                    url={references[5].url}
                  />.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="md:bg-white md:rounded-xl md:shadow-sm md:border md:border-slate-200 overflow-hidden lg:mt-auto">
              <div class="bg-rose-600 text-white px-4 py-3">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide">Differential</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="p-4 text-xs text-slate-600 space-y-2">
                <p>Lateral clavicle fracture, distal third clavicle fractures, scapula fracture, sternoclavicular injury.</p>
                <p>Do not miss <strong>type VI</strong> inferior dislocation — neurovascular assessment<RefLink
                    id="5"
                    text="Algorithm"
                    url={references[4].url}
                  />.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EXPERT -->
  <section id="expert" class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-800 via-slate-900 to-slate-800 py-12 scroll-mt-6">
    <div class="max-w-[1500px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-8">
        <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-full bg-amber-500/20 flex items-center justify-center text-amber-400">
          <Icon name="zap" size={28} strokeWidth={2} />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Expert perspective</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-400">My approach to AC joint dislocations</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-slate-800/50 backdrop-blur rounded-2xl border border-slate-700 p-6 md:p-8 max-w-4xl">
        <p class="text-slate-300 text-base leading-relaxed mb-6">
          High-grade AC injuries are common in Stockholm’s active population. I prioritise an accurate Rockwood assessment
          with quality Zanca views, then match treatment to <strong>horizontal stability</strong>, chronicity, and the patient’s
          aesthetic and performance goals — not to the radiograph alone.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-400 mb-3">Diagnostic approach</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          I explain upfront that <strong>type III</strong> injuries often do well without surgery, while acknowledging
          classification noise and shared decision-making for high-demand workers or visible deformity. I maintain a low
          threshold for MRI when symptoms suggest associated glenohumeral pathology in contact athletes<RefLink
            id="9"
            text="Associated lesions"
            url={references[8].url}
          />.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-400 mb-3">Surgical bias</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          When surgery is chosen, I prefer modern <strong>CC suspension constructs</strong> over hook plates in most acute
          scenarios to reduce subacromial morbidity and second-stage removal — consistent with current comparative
          literature<RefLink id="2" text="2025 review" url={references[1].url} /><RefLink id="6" text="Network MA" url={references[5].url} />.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="bg-white py-6 md:py-10 border-t border-slate-200 scroll-mt-6">
    <div class="max-w-[1500px] mx-auto px-3 sm:px-4 md:px-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <details class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-lg open:bg-sky-50 open:ring-1 open:ring-sky-200">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-4 font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span>Is surgery mandatory for a type V AC dislocation?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Not necessarily. A randomised trial found no difference at two years between hook plate fixation and structured
            physiotherapy for patients with type III and V injuries combined — shared decision-making is essential<RefLink
              id="8"
              text="JSES RCT"
              url={references[7].url}
            />.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-lg open:bg-sky-50 open:ring-1 open:ring-sky-200">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-4 font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span>Will the bump go away without surgery?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Often the cosmetic step-off persists after non-operative healing even when function is excellent. Surgery
            improves appearance more predictably but carries hardware-related trade-offs<RefLink
              id="1"
              text="Outcome data"
              url={references[0].url}
            />.
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group bg-slate-50 rounded-lg open:bg-sky-50 open:ring-1 open:ring-sky-200 md:col-span-2">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-4 font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm cursor-pointer list-none">
            <span>What if my injury is older than one month?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Delayed presentation reduces success of purely conservative care for some patients and may require graft-based
            reconstruction if surgery is chosen<RefLink id="11" text="Chronic cohort" url={references[10].url} /><RefLink
              id="9"
              text="Algorithm"
              url={references[8].url}
            />.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- REFERENCES -->
  <section id="references" class="bg-slate-100 py-6 md:py-8 scroll-mt-6">
    <div class="max-w-[1500px] mx-auto px-3 sm:px-4 md:px-6">
      <details class="group">
        <summary class="flex items-center gap-2 cursor-pointer text-slate-700 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide select-none">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 transition-transform group-open:rotate-90" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path>
          </svg>
          View all {references.length} references
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
          {references.map((ref, i) => (
            <a
              href={ref.url}
              class="text-xs text-slate-600 hover:text-sky-700 hover:bg-white p-2 rounded transition block"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              <span class="font-bold text-slate-400 mr-1">[{i + 1}]</span>
              {ref.text}
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-4 italic">Evidence list aligned with clinical synthesis. Updated {currentDate}.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <p class="text-center text-sm text-slate-500 py-6">
    <a href="/sjukdomar/axel/nyckelbensleden-ur-led" class="text-sky-600 hover:underline">Svenska: Nyckelbenet ur led</a>
  </p>

  <RefDrawer lang="en" />
</BaseLayout>
